tagDescription: Military leave N.W.Co.stations under command of Mr.A.McLeod,to storm Fort William. On arrival at Fort send back word for Indians to aid them.
Difficulty of obtaining provisions from Indians on account of scarcity of articles with which to trade.

Boats containing settlers meet Capt.McD. who tells of fate of Gov'r Semple and state of affairs in the Settlement.

Capt.D'O.'s plan to proceed from Lake La Prairie to Red River frustrated through timidity of voyageurs and lateness of season for navigation. Preparations made for wintering at the Lake.
